    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>rosemary leaves </strong>from their stems then chop them as finely as possible, discard the stems</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle the<strong> chopped rosemary</strong> over the <strong>fries</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp, golden and cooked through \u2013 these are your <strong>rosemary fries</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Finely dice 1/4 of your <strong>onion wedges</strong></p><p>Finely slice the<strong> remaining onion wedges</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion </strong>(save the diced onion for later!) with <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to very low and cook the onion until ready to serve, or until it has softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion is cooking, combine your <strong>mince</strong> with the <strong>diced onion </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Massage the meat with clean hands for 1 min (this helps them to hold their shape whilst cooking)</p><p>Divide the <strong>mince</strong> and shape into 1 patty per person</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fries have been in for 15-20 min, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>patty[ies] </strong>and press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Meanwhile, slice your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and put them in the oven for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, flip the <strong>patty[ies] </strong>and crumble your <strong>goats' cheese </strong>over them</p><p>Cover and reduce the heat to medium-high then cook for 5 min further until cooked through and charred (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy patty[ies]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-caramelised-onion-lean-beef-burger/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, spread a little <strong>butter </strong>on the <strong>warmed ciabatta</strong>, then top<strong> </strong>with a <strong>cheesy patty</strong>, some <strong>caramelised onion</strong>, a handful of <strong>salad </strong>and finally the <strong>warmed ciabatta[s] lid </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>goats' cheese & caramelised onion lean beef burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>rosemary fries </strong>and <strong>remaining salad </strong>to the side and dress the salad with the<strong> remaining balsamic vinegar </strong>and a splash of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
